# Changelog

All notable changes to the Quami project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.4.1] - 2025-11-22

### Added
- **Coming Soon Landing Page** - Beautiful single-page landing at quami.io:
  - Interactive Kwami blob in the center with glass morphism effects
  - Roadmap timeline with three milestones:
    - üöÄ July 2026: Public Alpha
    - üéØ September 2026: Beta Release
    - ‚ú® January 2027: v1.0 Stable
  - Call-to-action linking to kwami.io (Web3 app launching mainnet January 2025)
  - Fully responsive design for mobile and desktop
  - Dark mode support with adaptive glassmorphism
  - Gradient background with animated floating ghost emoji
  - Hover effects and smooth transitions throughout

### Changed
- Replaced incomplete app/pages/index.vue with coming soon page
- Updated README with development status and roadmap note

## [0.4.0] - 2025-11-19

### Removed
- **Complete Web3/Blockchain Removal** - Quami is now 100% web2:
  - Removed entire `solana/` directory including Anchor programs and Metaplex scripts
  - Removed wallet integration components and stores
  - Removed Kwami NFT minting functionality
  - Removed QWAMI token integration
  - Removed Solana dependencies (@solana/web3.js, @solana/spl-token, @coral-xyz/anchor, @metaplex-foundation/*)
  - Removed crypto libraries (bs58, crypto-js, buffer)
  - Removed web3-related server APIs (kwami mint, qwami balance)
  - Removed web3-related documentation files
  - Cleaned up configuration files (nuxt.config.ts, .env.sample)
  - Updated README and CONTRIBUTING docs to reflect web2-only focus

### Changed
- Quami is now a pure web2 application focused on privacy and AI features
- kwami.io will be the separate web3 project for blockchain functionality

## [0.3.0] - 2025-11-04

### Added

#### Solana Blockchain Integration
- **Kwami NFT System** - Complete NFT minting and management on Solana:
  - DNA-based uniqueness validation using SHA-256 hashing
  - On-chain DNA registry (max 1000 DNAs per registry)
  - Burn-and-remint flow for body configuration changes
  - Metadata-only updates for mind/soul changes
  - Metaplex standard compliance for wallet compatibility
- **QWAMI Token** - SPL token for AI service consumption:
  - 1 trillion max supply with 9 decimals
  - Base price of $0.01 USD per token
  - Mint/burn functionality with authority controls
  - Supply tracking (total minted/burned)
  - Token balance display in wallet

#### Anchor Programs (Rust)
- `solana/anchor/qwami-token/` - QWAMI token program:
  - Initialize, mint_tokens, burn_tokens instructions
  - Update base price and transfer authority
  - Supply cap enforcement
- `solana/anchor/kwami-nft/` - Kwami NFT program:
  - Initialize, mint_kwami, update_metadata, burn_kwami
  - DNA registry management
  - Uniqueness validation
  - Metaplex integration

#### Frontend State Management
- `app/stores/kwami-nft.ts` - NFT state management:
  - DNA calculation from body configuration
  - Minting flow state machine (9 states)
  - Progress tracking (0-100%)
  - Update flow with DNA change detection
  - Owned NFTs tracking
- Enhanced `app/stores/wallet.ts`:
  - QWAMI balance fetching
  - Kwami NFT detection via Metaplex
  - Collection filtering (verified NFTs only)
  - Auto-refresh on account changes

#### Minting UI Components
- `app/components/Quami/Kwami/Mint/Index.vue` - Main minting interface
- `app/components/Quami/Kwami/Mint/DNAPreview.vue` - Real-time DNA display with uniqueness check
- `app/components/Quami/Kwami/Mint/MetadataForm.vue` - Name (50 chars) and description (500 chars) inputs
- `app/components/Quami/Kwami/Mint/MintButton.vue` - Gradient button with loading states
- Added "Mint" tab to Kwami component interface
- Updated wallet balances to display QWAMI and Kwami NFT counts

#### Backend API Routes
- `server/api/kwami/mint.post.ts` - NFT minting with DNA validation and Arweave upload
- `server/api/kwami/update.post.ts` - Metadata updates with burn/remint detection
- `server/api/kwami/check-dna.post.ts` - On-chain DNA uniqueness validation
- `server/api/qwami/balance.get.ts` - QWAMI token balance queries

#### Metaplex & Arweave Integration
- `solana/metaplex/utils/uploadToArweave.ts` - Comprehensive upload utilities:
  - File upload to Arweave via Bundlr
  - JSON metadata upload
  - Complete NFT asset upload workflow
  - Funding and balance checking
- `solana/metaplex/utils/createCollection.ts` - Collection initialization
- `solana/scripts/initialize-collection.sh` - Automated deployment script
- Collection metadata configuration

#### Utility Functions
- `app/utils/kwami/calculateKwamiDNA.ts` - SHA-256 DNA computation from body config:
  - Includes: spikes, time, rotation, colors, resolution, skin, shininess, wireframe, baseScale, opacity
  - Excludes: background, audio, mind, soul
  - Normalized JSON serialization for consistent hashing
- `app/utils/kwami/prepareKwamiMetadata.ts` - Metaplex-standard metadata formatting

#### Documentation
- `docs/DNA_SYSTEM.md` - Complete DNA system documentation:
  - Algorithm explanation
  - Security considerations
  - On-chain registry structure
  - Burn-and-remint vs. metadata-only updates
  - Best practices and FAQ
- `docs/KWAMI_NFT_MINTING.md` - User guide for minting:
  - Step-by-step minting process
  - Wallet setup instructions
  - Troubleshooting common issues
  - Managing and updating NFTs
- `docs/QWAMI_TOKEN.md` - Token economics documentation:
  - Tokenomics model and distribution
  - Utility and consumption mechanics
  - Staking rewards and governance
  - Integration guide for developers
- `solana/SETUP.md` - Development environment setup
- `solana/README.md` - Programs overview and architecture
- Program-specific READMEs with deployment instructions

#### Project Structure
- `solana/` directory with organized subdirectories:
  - `anchor/` for Rust programs
  - `metaplex/` for NFT utilities
  - `scripts/` for deployment and management
  - `collection/` for collection metadata

### Changed

- Enhanced Phantom wallet integration with QWAMI and NFT detection
- Updated wallet event listeners to sync blockchain data
- Expanded `.env.sample` with Solana configuration variables
- Added Solana dependencies to `package.json`:
  - @coral-xyz/anchor
  - @metaplex-foundation/js
  - @solana/spl-token
  - bs58
  - crypto-js

### Technical Details

- **DNA Registry**: PDA-based storage with 1000 DNA capacity per registry
- **NFT Storage**: Permanent storage on Arweave for metadata and assets
- **Token Supply**: 1 trillion QWAMI max, 9 decimals, mintable/burnable
- **Blockchain**: Solana devnet (configurable for mainnet)
- **Collection**: Metaplex certified collection for verified NFTs
- **Security**: SHA-256 collision-resistant hashing, authority-controlled minting

## [0.2.0] - 2025-11-03

### Added

- Comprehensive CONTRIBUTING.md with development guidelines and commit conventions
- Complete Kwami body parameter controls from playground:
  - Geometry & Motion controls (spikes, time, rotation, resolution)
  - Scale & Camera orbit controls
  - Material properties (opacity, shininess, light intensity, wireframe)
  - Audio effects controls (frequency modulation, time modulation, analyzer)
  - Interaction controls (touch effects, state transitions)
  - Randomize, export GLTF, and reset to defaults functionality
- @alexcolls/nuxt-ux@0.6.0 npm package with 67+ reusable UI components
- Auto-imported Common components (CommonBtn, CommonMagicWindow, etc.)
- Documentation folder structure (docs/) for better organization

### Changed

- Migrated from local Common components to @alexcolls/nuxt-ux package
- Moved submodules to app/modules/ directory for better organization
- Updated Kwami import paths to use @kwami alias
- Replaced nuxt-themes submodule with @alexcolls/nuxt-ux npm package
- Updated README with accurate paths, versions, and comprehensive feature list
- Fixed Kwami body component API compatibility with core library
- Updated wallet components with troubleshooting documentation
- Enhanced blob animation and Audio core implementation

### Fixed

- Kwami body component API compatibility (direct property access)
- @kwami import resolution errors
- Main README emoji (sun ‚òÄÔ∏è)
- Camera access using getCamera() method
- Scale access via mesh.scale.setScalar()
- Locale file extensions in nuxt-ux module (.ts ‚Üí .js)

### Removed

- Local app/components/Common folder (migrated to nuxt-ux package)
- nuxt-themes submodule (replaced with nuxt-ux npm package)

## [0.1.0] - 2025-10-20

### Added

- Initial release of Quami - 3D interactive AI companion application
- Integration with Kwami v2.0.0 as git submodule
- 3D interactive blob visualization with real-time morphing
- Audio-reactive animations with multiple skin options (tricolor, zebra)
- Voice interaction capabilities with speech-to-text and text-to-speech
- Natural language AI conversation system
- User authentication via Supabase (email and wallet)
- Wallet integration with Solana blockchain
- Multi-language support (English, French, Spanish) via i18n
- Profile management and session persistence
- Dark mode and theme customization
- Responsive UI with Nuxt UI components
- Server-side API routes for backend functionality

### Architecture

- Built on Nuxt.js 4 with SSR disabled for optimal client-side performance
- Kwami library integrated as git submodule at `app/modules/@kwami/`
- State management with Pinia and persisted state support
- Three.js for 3D graphics rendering
- Supabase for backend services and authentication
- TypeScript for type safety across the application

### Technical Details

- Node server preset for production builds
- Vite-based development environment
- ESLint configuration with stylistic rules
- Optimized dependency bundling for Web3 libraries
- CORS-enabled API routes for external integrations
- View transitions for smooth page navigation
